<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 5:26PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Davidson,
northwestern Montgomery, western Randolph and northeastern Stanly
Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 525 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
extending from 7 miles northwest of Linwood to Granite Quarry to
near Coddle Creek Reservoir. Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
High Point, Lexington, Badin Lake, Thomasville, Linwood, Trinity,
Badin, Denton, Richfield and New London.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
